  <compounddef id="EMPTYRAMDISK" kind="page">
    <compoundname>EMPTYRAMDISK</compoundname>
    <title>EMPTYRAMDISK$ Function</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">EMPTYRAMDISK$(size-megabytes)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Creates a <bold>RAM-backed block device and formats it as RetroFS</bold>. The parameter is the size of the new device in megabytes. Returns the device name on success.</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<sect1 id="EMPTYRAMDISK_1examples-94_1s1"><sect2 id="EMPTYRAMDISK_1examples-94_1s2"><sect3 id="EMPTYRAMDISK_1examples-94">
<title>Examples</title><para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">REM<sp/>Create<sp/>a<sp/>1GB<sp/>RetroFS<sp/>ramdisk</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">RD$<sp/>=<sp/>EMPTYRAMDISK$(1024)</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">MOUNT<sp/>&quot;/ramdisk&quot;,<sp/>RD$,<sp/>&quot;rfs&quot;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>&quot;Created<sp/>RAM<sp/>disk&quot;</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
</sect3></sect2></sect1>
<sect1 id="EMPTYRAMDISK_1notes-93_1s1"><sect2 id="EMPTYRAMDISK_1notes-93_1s2"><sect3 id="EMPTYRAMDISK_1notes-93">
<title>Notes</title><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>The ram disk block size is always 512</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Device names are automatically assigned by the system (e.g. <computeroutput>&quot;ram0&quot;</computeroutput>, <computeroutput>&quot;ram1&quot;</computeroutput>).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Contents are volatile and cleared when the system shuts down or discards the device.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><bold>See also:</bold> <ref refid="MOUNT" kindref="compound">MOUNT</ref> </para>
</sect3></sect2></sect1>
